1
00:00:33,291 --> 00:00:34,500
What the...?

2
00:00:34,916 --> 00:00:38,416
So Deus is sending
us text messages now?

3
00:00:43,083 --> 00:00:47,541
"The ability to add diary
keepers." That can happen?

4
00:01:04,166 --> 00:01:05,125
More keepers?

5
00:01:05,208 --> 00:01:06,791
You got to be kidding me.

6
00:01:06,875 --> 00:01:11,833
♪ opening song ♪

7
00:02:47,083 --> 00:02:48,708
So, what kind of
knowledge did the Lord High

8
00:02:48,791 --> 00:02:50,583
Referee drop on you guys?

9
00:02:51,083 --> 00:02:52,000
Uh...

10
00:02:52,083 --> 00:02:53,416
Give me a sec.

11
00:02:54,041 --> 00:02:56,500
Hey, Kousaka mind if
I borrow your cell phone?

12
00:02:56,583 --> 00:02:57,916
Nuh-uh!

13
00:02:59,833 --> 00:03:01,250
Just be careful, yeah?

14
00:03:01,333 --> 00:03:04,458
That bad boy's a full-fledged
Future Diary now!

15
00:03:04,541 --> 00:03:07,291
But, with great power
comes great responsibility.

16
00:03:07,375 --> 00:03:09,500
Break that phone
and my ass is dead.

17
00:03:09,583 --> 00:03:11,541
What the balls
are you doing, man?!

18
00:03:13,333 --> 00:03:15,291
Yup!
I'm checking out!

19
00:03:17,458 --> 00:03:19,125
Well, guess I was right.

20
00:03:19,208 --> 00:03:21,791
And for Kousaka's sake,
I'm glad you were!

21
00:03:21,875 --> 00:03:23,166
In that case...

22
00:03:23,250 --> 00:03:25,791
Eighth's diary has to
offer server functionality.

23
00:03:25,875 --> 00:03:28,208
Grow a pair already, would ya?

24
00:03:29,166 --> 00:03:31,416
How is he still
alive after that?

25
00:03:31,916 --> 00:03:34,333
At first blush, it would seem
that Eighth is "spawning"

26
00:03:34,416 --> 00:03:37,708
new keepers but the truth
is far more pedestrian.

27
00:03:38,541 --> 00:03:41,416
The server is the
one true Future Diary.

28
00:03:42,041 --> 00:03:45,583
All the others are mere
knockoffs, subordinate to it.

29
00:03:45,666 --> 00:03:46,583
That would be the reason you

30
00:03:46,666 --> 00:03:48,583
didn't coil into
oblivion just now.

31
00:03:48,666 --> 00:03:50,250
That so wasn't cool, man!

32
00:03:50,333 --> 00:03:51,291
How am I supposed to bask

33
00:03:51,375 --> 00:03:53,166
in my future
rockitude now, huh?!

34
00:03:53,250 --> 00:03:55,416
We couldn't risk the
enemy using that information

35
00:03:55,500 --> 00:03:56,708
to keep tabs on us.

36
00:03:56,791 --> 00:03:59,291
Dude, let a brother
back up his crap first!

37
00:03:59,791 --> 00:04:01,458
Sorry about that.

38
00:04:04,083 --> 00:04:05,833
The plot thickens?

39
00:04:05,916 --> 00:04:09,291
Three days from now
they invade my house!

40
00:04:09,375 --> 00:04:12,041
Tracking us from afar
doesn't longer an option.

41
00:04:12,125 --> 00:04:14,458
They're going to be
anxious to make a move.

42
00:04:14,541 --> 00:04:16,166
What should I do?

43
00:04:16,250 --> 00:04:18,416
I can't rely on Yuno.

44
00:04:21,291 --> 00:04:26,000
You didn't just do
that... Darling why?

45
00:04:26,666 --> 00:04:28,458
Screw you.

46
00:04:32,250 --> 00:04:36,208
I know it was the
right decision but still,

47
00:04:36,291 --> 00:04:38,708
how am I supposed
to fend for myself?!

48
00:04:38,791 --> 00:04:42,708
The question is, how do we keep
our sundry enemies at bay?

49
00:04:42,791 --> 00:04:45,625
Nishijima assigning some
guards would be a fair start.

50
00:04:45,708 --> 00:04:48,000
We need to stash Yuki where
they're not gonna look.

51
00:04:48,083 --> 00:04:50,083
A little bird told me that
Kousaka's house would

52
00:04:50,166 --> 00:04:51,541
be the perfect spot to hide him.

53
00:04:51,625 --> 00:04:52,583
Wha?

54
00:04:52,666 --> 00:04:54,041
Alright then
everything's settled.

55
00:04:54,125 --> 00:04:55,333
What do mean it's settled?!

56
00:04:55,416 --> 00:04:57,916
Does that plan get
your seal of approval?

57
00:04:59,416 --> 00:05:03,541
You mean, you guys are
really gonna help me out?

58
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:06,541
All due respect,
man, but tough titty...

59
00:05:07,083 --> 00:05:08,666
You seem a bit shocked and awed.

60
00:05:08,750 --> 00:05:11,625
What, you didn't think we were
gonna do you a solid Yuki?

61
00:05:14,375 --> 00:05:15,208
No phone.

62
00:05:15,291 --> 00:05:16,875
Just tell us what's in your gut.

63
00:05:16,958 --> 00:05:19,250
"We'll show you ours
if you show us yours,"

64
00:05:19,333 --> 00:05:22,000
which is a crude idiom,
but apropos.

65
00:05:22,083 --> 00:05:25,375
So do you want us to help you,
or mind our own business?

66
00:05:27,125 --> 00:05:28,333
Uh...

67
00:05:28,416 --> 00:05:29,500
I...

68
00:05:30,625 --> 00:05:32,458
I can't do this on my own.

69
00:05:32,541 --> 00:05:35,625
Good, because we
weren't about to let you.

70
00:05:42,458 --> 00:05:43,958
I called up our benefactor.

71
00:05:44,041 --> 00:05:45,416
You'll have
round-the-clock protection

72
00:05:45,500 --> 00:05:47,125
for the next three days.

73
00:05:47,208 --> 00:05:49,791
If anything happens,
radio for help.

74
00:05:49,875 --> 00:05:50,625
Yeah.

75
00:05:50,708 --> 00:05:51,833
I got it.

76
00:05:51,916 --> 00:05:53,500
We'll come up with a
plan to fight off those

77
00:05:53,583 --> 00:05:56,750
three subordinate diary users
once we're at Kousaka's.

78
00:05:56,833 --> 00:05:58,666
Yuno's still an issue, though.

79
00:05:58,750 --> 00:06:00,375
Her diary feeds her a constant

80
00:06:00,458 --> 00:06:03,125
drip of information as to
your whereabouts.

81
00:06:03,500 --> 00:06:06,458
But we have no such
window into her doings.

82
00:06:06,541 --> 00:06:09,208
Long as she holds the tactical
high-ground we have to brace

83
00:06:09,291 --> 00:06:13,166
for the possibility
that she could

84
00:06:13,250 --> 00:06:13,791
blindside us at
any given moment.

85
00:06:13,875 --> 00:06:14,958
Blindside us how?

86
00:06:15,041 --> 00:06:17,250
Yuki, she might regard
your recent escape

87
00:06:17,333 --> 00:06:19,583
as an irreparable betrayal.

88
00:06:20,041 --> 00:06:23,583
She might want me dead?!

89
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:35,250
Who is it?

90
00:06:44,375 --> 00:06:45,291
Just in time.

91
00:06:45,375 --> 00:06:46,875
Grab a plate!

92
00:06:46,958 --> 00:06:48,541
Heya, Mom.

93
00:06:51,125 --> 00:06:53,458
The last time Mom and
I had dinner together

94
00:06:53,541 --> 00:06:56,458
we owed the meal
to psycho-stalker.

95
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,500
So... um...

96
00:07:01,583 --> 00:07:03,125
Go ahead.

97
00:07:03,208 --> 00:07:04,708
Well...

98
00:07:04,791 --> 00:07:07,166
Aren't you going to ask why
the police wanted Yuno and me?

99
00:07:07,250 --> 00:07:08,583
I mean...

100
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:12,916
Awesome segue, Einstein.

101
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:14,541
Tell ya what.

102
00:07:14,625 --> 00:07:16,083
You've been through
a rough patch lately,

103
00:07:16,166 --> 00:07:18,583
and I'm only going to make it
worse by picking away at it.

104
00:07:18,666 --> 00:07:21,375
If you want to unburden your
soul, then knock yourself out.

105
00:07:21,458 --> 00:07:24,708
Otherwise, I'll wait 'til
you're ready to clue me in.

106
00:07:25,750 --> 00:07:27,416
Thanks for being cool.

107
00:07:27,500 --> 00:07:28,375
That said...

108
00:07:28,458 --> 00:07:29,416
Huh?

109
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:31,458
Don't leave me
in the dark forever.

110
00:07:31,541 --> 00:07:33,208
We got a deal?

111
00:07:33,583 --> 00:07:34,750
Yeah.

112
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:40,000
Uh, question.

113
00:07:40,083 --> 00:07:43,583
Isn't that, like,
a lot of potato salad?

114
00:07:43,666 --> 00:07:44,958
Totally.

115
00:07:45,041 --> 00:07:47,333
The three of us would've
exploded if we ate all that.

116
00:07:47,416 --> 00:07:48,875
Three of us?

117
00:07:53,458 --> 00:07:55,333
Yuno couldn't stick
around tonight.

118
00:07:55,416 --> 00:07:56,375
She was here?!

119
00:07:56,458 --> 00:07:57,375
Duh.

120
00:07:57,458 --> 00:07:58,916
Who do you think
made this dinner?

121
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:00,583
She said you'd
need to be well-fed

122
00:08:00,666 --> 00:08:02,625
for what she has
in store for you.

123
00:08:02,708 --> 00:08:05,708
Got to make sure you
rise to the occasion, huh?

124
00:08:08,291 --> 00:08:10,500
Let's go over
the plan, shall we?

125
00:08:10,833 --> 00:08:12,791
First, we deposit the
redoubtable Yuki

126
00:08:12,875 --> 00:08:14,916
at Kousaka's house
for safekeeping.

127
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,708
Nishijima sends over cops.

128
00:08:16,791 --> 00:08:18,375
We'll be guarded
round-the-clock.

129
00:08:18,458 --> 00:08:20,041
What good are the
police going to be

130
00:08:20,125 --> 00:08:21,833
against people who
know the future?

131
00:08:21,916 --> 00:08:22,958
Let's just say.

132
00:08:23,041 --> 00:08:25,125
I've taken all that
well into account.

133
00:08:25,208 --> 00:08:25,833
Yo...

134
00:08:25,916 --> 00:08:27,125
Home, twelve o'clock.

135
00:08:27,208 --> 00:08:28,625
Good.

136
00:08:28,958 --> 00:08:29,666
--What?!
--What?!

137
00:08:29,750 --> 00:08:30,833
Not too shabby.

138
00:08:30,916 --> 00:08:32,500
Can I just drive
through the gate?

139
00:08:32,583 --> 00:08:34,208
Sure.

140
00:08:34,666 --> 00:08:36,916
So all this is
Kousaka's front yard?!

141
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:38,625
You're filthy
frigging rich, dude!

142
00:08:38,708 --> 00:08:39,666
Gramps was rich.

143
00:08:39,750 --> 00:08:41,708
I'm filthy frigging lucky.

144
00:08:41,791 --> 00:08:44,583
My plan requires ample
space if it's going to work.

145
00:08:44,666 --> 00:08:47,625
After we've lured the enemy to
this modest homestead they will

146
00:08:47,708 --> 00:08:50,375
soon find themselves
hoist by their own petard.

147
00:08:50,458 --> 00:08:51,958
Observe.

148
00:08:52,041 --> 00:08:54,208
How's a cell phone
tower gonna help us?

149
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:57,000
What if it were to malfunction
when they attack?

150
00:08:57,083 --> 00:08:58,041
Oh yeah!

151
00:08:58,125 --> 00:08:59,291
If the tower doesn't work,

152
00:08:59,375 --> 00:09:01,500
they can't get updates
from Eighth's server!

153
00:09:01,583 --> 00:09:02,708
Exactly.

154
00:09:02,791 --> 00:09:05,125
They won't be privy
to the future anymore.

155
00:09:07,750 --> 00:09:09,125
Granted, this will only work

156
00:09:09,208 --> 00:09:11,875
against those with
subordinate diaries.

157
00:09:12,875 --> 00:09:14,750
This is a little something
I threw together

158
00:09:14,833 --> 00:09:17,458
so we can disable
the tower from up here.

159
00:09:24,916 --> 00:09:25,875
Heads up, guys.

160
00:09:25,958 --> 00:09:26,791
Eighth's underlings
are gonna make

161
00:09:26,875 --> 00:09:28,875
a play for us in three minutes.

162
00:09:30,375 --> 00:09:31,708
Squad A to HQ.

163
00:09:31,791 --> 00:09:34,000
We've got eyes on the targets...
they're on the property.

164
00:09:34,083 --> 00:09:35,458
They're here!

165
00:09:35,541 --> 00:09:37,000
Hands at the ready, Yuki.

166
00:09:37,083 --> 00:09:40,166
But don't flip those switches
'til I give you the word.

167
00:09:40,875 --> 00:09:41,416
Well?

168
00:09:41,500 --> 00:09:42,250
See them?!

169
00:09:42,333 --> 00:09:43,625
Not yet.

170
00:09:43,708 --> 00:09:45,000
But the fight is still young.

171
00:09:45,083 --> 00:09:46,666
We need to make sure
they're well away from the

172
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:48,833
entrance so they
don't simply retreat.

173
00:09:51,333 --> 00:09:52,125
The hell?!

174
00:09:52,208 --> 00:09:53,166
Power's out!

175
00:09:53,250 --> 00:09:55,375
They're inside flip the switch!

176
00:09:59,083 --> 00:10:00,250
I don't want to be a buzz-kill,

177
00:10:00,333 --> 00:10:02,416
but I'm still rocking
three bars over here!

178
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:03,958
Of course!

179
00:10:04,375 --> 00:10:06,833
No power's running to the box!

180
00:10:06,916 --> 00:10:08,958
It's like they knew in advance!

181
00:10:11,333 --> 00:10:12,916
Noo... no way.

182
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:14,833
We were the only ones
who knew what was up.

183
00:10:14,916 --> 00:10:16,291
Just the five of us!

184
00:10:16,375 --> 00:10:17,833
No one else!

185
00:10:19,500 --> 00:10:21,166
Unless.

186
00:10:23,916 --> 00:10:25,958
Are you trying
to get us killed?!

187
00:10:26,041 --> 00:10:26,541
Hey!

188
00:10:26,625 --> 00:10:27,500
Found ya!

189
00:10:27,583 --> 00:10:28,375
Aw!

190
00:10:28,458 --> 00:10:30,083
You've had me worried to death!

191
00:10:30,166 --> 00:10:32,291
But, have no fear, honey-bun!

192
00:10:32,375 --> 00:10:34,583
I'm gonna save you!

193
00:10:39,541 --> 00:10:40,916
Oh, I've missed you, baby!

194
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,666
What the hell is she doing here?

195
00:10:42,750 --> 00:10:44,875
Is she gonna drag me off again?!

196
00:10:44,958 --> 00:10:46,583
Yuki, Look at me!

197
00:10:46,666 --> 00:10:49,416
Yuki, I'm here for you!

198
00:10:49,875 --> 00:10:52,333
Hey. Maybe you should
come up here, Yuno.

199
00:10:52,416 --> 00:10:54,291
Yuki told me he'd prefer that.

200
00:10:54,375 --> 00:10:56,208
Are you nuts?!

201
00:10:56,291 --> 00:10:57,750
Kousaka and I will
head over to the

202
00:10:57,833 --> 00:11:00,041
cell phone tower and
disable it manually.

203
00:11:00,125 --> 00:11:01,333
I know it's asking a lot,

204
00:11:01,416 --> 00:11:03,125
but you need to keep
that girl placated.

205
00:11:03,208 --> 00:11:04,750
We can't have her running amok.

206
00:11:04,833 --> 00:11:05,916
Why me?

207
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,125
Step lively now.

208
00:11:07,208 --> 00:11:08,583
We haven't a moment to waste.

209
00:11:08,666 --> 00:11:10,250
You first.

210
00:11:12,625 --> 00:11:16,041
Says here it'll take them thirty
minutes to knock out the tower.

211
00:11:16,125 --> 00:11:18,833
We just have to run
down the clock 'til they do.

212
00:11:19,458 --> 00:11:20,833
Yuki, darling.

213
00:11:20,916 --> 00:11:22,666
Why'd you bind my hands?

214
00:11:23,416 --> 00:11:27,250
'Cause without them tied,
you scare the crap outta me.

215
00:11:29,333 --> 00:11:32,333
Wouldn't I be more useful
with my hands untied?

216
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:37,083
Nishijima!

217
00:11:37,166 --> 00:11:39,041
Son of a bitch!

218
00:11:39,125 --> 00:11:40,750
Ah, check it out, Marco!

219
00:11:40,833 --> 00:11:42,083
There's Yuki.

220
00:11:42,166 --> 00:11:44,125
That drab little pork-chop
second from the left.

221
00:11:44,208 --> 00:11:45,250
C'mon, Ai.

222
00:11:45,333 --> 00:11:47,500
He's no more than
tofu on a good day.

223
00:11:47,583 --> 00:11:49,125
Don't be a jerk... He's
lasted this long, hasn't he?

224
00:11:49,208 --> 00:11:51,083
Oh crap!
How'd they get here so fast?!

225
00:11:51,166 --> 00:11:52,458
Give it up.

226
00:11:52,875 --> 00:11:54,666
You may have got
the drop on me once.

227
00:11:54,750 --> 00:11:58,625
But I'm about to open up a can
of police brutality on your ass!

228
00:11:59,708 --> 00:12:01,750
Yeah about that!

229
00:12:02,916 --> 00:12:04,708
Night-night, little piggy!

230
00:12:04,791 --> 00:12:06,041
Checking that highlight reel,

231
00:12:06,125 --> 00:12:08,458
it's clear you zigged when
you should have zagged!

232
00:12:09,291 --> 00:12:12,041
You and your boner
for counterattacks.

233
00:12:12,125 --> 00:12:14,000
Not that it's gonna save
your ass either way

234
00:12:14,083 --> 00:12:17,083
but I'm gonna give you
a sneak-peek, pretty boy!

235
00:12:18,166 --> 00:12:19,291
Check it out!

236
00:12:19,375 --> 00:12:21,500
The Undefeated Champion Diary!

237
00:12:21,583 --> 00:12:23,416
It tells me when to bust
out a counter attack

238
00:12:23,500 --> 00:12:26,041
and plant whatever
chump's in my way!

239
00:12:26,125 --> 00:12:29,333
You wanna come down here
and give it a closer look?

240
00:12:32,750 --> 00:12:34,125
Goodness.

241
00:12:34,208 --> 00:12:36,458
So Marco and Ai have made
it into the mansion already?

242
00:12:36,541 --> 00:12:37,750
Very well!

243
00:12:37,833 --> 00:12:39,875
In that case, just keep
an eye on them for me.

244
00:12:39,958 --> 00:12:41,916
Would you, Ta?

245
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:43,625
Yeah...
Sure thing.

246
00:12:43,708 --> 00:12:45,833
Everybody!
Run for it!

247
00:12:46,333 --> 00:12:47,875
Shouldn't we be
chasing after them?

248
00:12:47,958 --> 00:12:49,791
No point in breaking
a sweat, Mar.

249
00:12:49,875 --> 00:12:51,541
He's not getting away.

250
00:12:51,625 --> 00:12:53,083
Hello, boys.

251
00:12:53,583 --> 00:12:54,458
Don't forget.

252
00:12:54,541 --> 00:12:56,083
I've got the details on any guy

253
00:12:56,166 --> 00:12:58,416
I'm gonna flirt with,
including where.

254
00:13:00,208 --> 00:13:04,041
First is a little young but a
gal could do a lot worse.

255
00:13:08,666 --> 00:13:09,958
What'd I tell ya?

256
00:13:10,041 --> 00:13:11,458
How'd they find us?!

257
00:13:11,541 --> 00:13:13,333
I'll buy you guys some time!

258
00:13:13,791 --> 00:13:16,875
Props for the moxie,
honey but I don't like girls!

259
00:13:17,583 --> 00:13:19,083
Sorry!

260
00:13:20,458 --> 00:13:21,333
Mao, no!

261
00:13:21,416 --> 00:13:22,333
Are you okay?!

262
00:13:22,416 --> 00:13:24,708
We have to keep climbing, Yuki!

263
00:13:30,833 --> 00:13:33,208
